    {
      "id": "bd00356f_125496d4",
      "file_path": "docker/build_docker.sh",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 81,
      "message": "I have some other suggestion, that would make less operations needed, but cause minimal change in dockerfile/docker build command.\n\nYou can actually build docker from top level directory with command like `docker build . -t onap/testsuite -f docker/Dockerfile` but Dockerfile would need to modify its COPY statements to following:\n```\nCOPY docker/lighttpd.conf /etc/lighttpd/lighttpd.conf\nCOPY docker/authorization /etc/lighttpd/authorization\n```\n\nAfter such improvements, you can even purge .dockerignore quite a lot, thus reducing transferred build cache greatly and also reducing manual steps needed.\n\nPlease consider this solution :)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5550,
        "name": "Konrad Banka",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kbanka.os@gmail.com",
        "username": "kbanka"
      },
      "updated": "2019-11-18 13:08:04.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
